line 60 mp.py reads:
 head_file = self.__mf.get_output(unit=iu)
 it should be:
 head_file = self.__mf.get_output(unit=iu) if head_file is None else head_file

similarly line 71 should read:
 budget_file = self.__mf.get_output(unit=iu) if budget_file is None else budget_file

This arises as a Modflow object must be passed to the Modpath object in order to create the ModpathBas object: (lines 76 and 77 of mpbas.py) A dummy model (with a simple lpf) can be passed instead, but the users files must be used. I am doing this for speed
